title.narrative: Level of frequent, positive and substantive references to DEDI's role in Denmark and Egypt
Mutual understanding between Denmark and Egypt has been enhanced through DEDI's activities within the fields of politics and democratization, culture as a means of participation, and media.
Platforms for DEDI-initiated dialogue established in Denmark and Egypt

Dialogue Forums have been held inviting 10-15 youth from each country with a focus on dialogue and dialogical methods. Methodology and involvement of Dialogue Ambassadors have been essential. In 2014, a session took place on democracy in Egypt.

1. The civic education programme trained 300 young people from the governorates of Giza, Menufiyya and Faoyum. 2. Danish Egyptian Political Party Network continued capacity development and the exchange programme for youth politicians representing Egyptian and Danish political parties. 3. Female parliamentarians trained in cooperation with American University in Cairo. 4. Annual Youth Exchange Programme organised a youth conference in cooperation with the Swedish Institute in Alexandria, gathering 40 young people from Europe and the Middle East to discuss topics such as gender and politics.
Platforms for DEDI-initiated dialogue established in Denmark and Egypt, contributing to open, democratic and inclusive development relating to thematic priorities of politics, culture and media.
